            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Διονύσιος"><seg part="I"><supplied reason="lost">Διο</supplied>νύσι<supplied reason="lost">ο</supplied></seg></name></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><space extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <persName type="divine" ref="#Demeter"><name nymRef="#Δαμάτηρ">Δάματ<supplied reason="lost">ρι</supplied></name></persName> 
                        <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">καὶ</supplied> <persName type="divine" ref="#Kore"><name nymRef="#Κόρα"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">Κόραι</supplied></name></persName> <w lemma="ἀνατίθημι"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ἀνέθηκε</supplied></w>.
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="2"><lem resp="#jmr2012"><supplied reason="lost" cert="low">καὶ Κόραι ἀνέθηκε</supplied></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#white1973"><supplied reason="lost">καὶ Κόραι</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
               </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Dionysios <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> à Dèmèter <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">et à Korè a consacré</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Dionysios <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> to Demeter <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">and to Kore dedicated</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Dionysios <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> a Demetra e <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">a Kore ha dedicato</supplied>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>As <bibl><ptr target="#jmr2012"/></bibl>, puts it, the name Dionysios, which is plausibly restored, might belong to the dedicant (hence nominative)
                    or to the person whose statue was dedicated by someone else (hence accusative).
                It depends on the width of the original base, as well as of the divine name or names to be restored at l. 2, with or without a verb.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
